subSubSection.paragraph:
Diagnosis.
Male of this species can be distinguished from other species of subgenus 

Gnathonomia

by the following: hind femur strongly developed, swollen; hind tibia with a weakly C-shaped projection apically (
Fig. 3e
); scutellum shiny, with sparse large punctures (
Fig. 3c
); apical margin of T1–5 with yellowish bands, and band on T1 narrower than that on T2–5 (band on T1 absent sometimes) (
Fig. 3f
).

